Reference-contexts: Due to the large number of protocols at different network layers, it is often infeasible to build and measure all of them. A better alternative is to trace the behaviors of existing implementations and apply the lessons learned to evaluate new designs. From wireless network traces <ref> (Noble, Nguyen, Satyanarayanan, and Katz 1996) </ref>, we can improve our understanding of the wireless channel behavior, develop realistic models, and validate them. Traces also provide us a way to reproduce realistic network and mobile environments for comparing protocols and algorithms.
